<subSubSection id="004660E89AF2AD3E523FA00ACAEE31E7" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9ADBA729F5FB7D386208256A00028E68" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66AC6B76612ABF142F148A8F55176E20" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
Maxime affine 
<taxonomicName id="E652F6378EE10B9653CCD1C2CAA4034E" authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 549. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ammannii" order="Solanales" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ammannii">
<emphasis id="E35CB7638C65A7BC906FA1C10383427B" italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Convolvulus ammannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desr. sed floribus terminalibus solitariis vel in cymis terminalibus dispositis, sepalis corollaque longioribus, caule lignosa distincta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77EB212BCB9A0695BAC587FA75C733B9" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" type="type">
<paragraph id="2072FD7F8FEC014A8876CED1A0DF7DAC" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4EF70A4B073ED4B2989867B6500DF374" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
CHINA, Shensi, Hancheng Sian, 1914, 
<emphasis id="46265E6D757D8FAE7D55FBC99D45B041" italics="true" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">W. Purdom</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype K001067037!; isotypes K!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ABFA107F2B81A5270600D105C177FF9E" lastPageId="152" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" type="description">
<paragraph id="68A9E1FA2CC458F9775B0A28ADE0AC6E" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3CDE652029B67AC9CE3339C9C90A47B" lastPageId="152" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="151" pageNumber="152">
Much branched perennial undershrub with erect stems to c. 20 cm; old stems woody and rigid, weakly divaricate, up to 10 mm thick, new growth herbaceous grey-sericeous. Leaves sessile, 4-40 
<normalizedToken id="D4C2998801C9CFC9555A5D3717723ADE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, linear, acute, grey-sericeous. Flowers terminal, solitary or in small dichasial cymes, the branches appressed pilose, up to 6 mm long; bracts and bracteoles not clearly differentiated, 1-10 
<normalizedToken id="02EC03A7769B17EB1D49F3EA967EE0ED" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, linear; peduncles not differentiated from the stem; pedicels 1-3 mm; outer se 
<pageBreakToken id="9162BADF92F4D3DD8DE5F4BA8C526F1D" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" start="start">pals</pageBreakToken>
6-7 
<normalizedToken id="45CDDC1F3DB0DB46EC3DBE7CDA1F403B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3.5 mm, elliptic to obovate, caudate, densely pilose; inner sepals 5 
<normalizedToken id="BE225A0AC2E37DF04964E5259B0740E4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, ovate, caudate, convex, somewhat scarious, thinly pilose; corolla 1.5-2 cm, unlobed, midpetaline bands pilose; filaments 4 mm long, glabrous, anthers 2 mm, sagittate; ovary 2 mm long, conical, comose, style pilose below, divided 3-7 mm above base, persistent; stigmas 1.75 mm; capsule 2 
<normalizedToken id="247325B955EEAD38610D56113E46988B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5 mm, pubescent, capped by the persistent style; seeds 1.5 
<normalizedToken id="E767148EA68A0256AE1DABBC075D9EB9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, conical with a rounded base, pubescent, blackish-brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="849CF38DCEE38566C97A80213E568AA1" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CABD17B393700FAEDCBB4905F63CC17B" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2464E980257A85AC1EB1969FEF6DED79" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
China: Shanxi, Hanchengsian; Henan, Loyan, Shan Xian, Sanmenxia Gorge, on left bank of Yellow River (
<emphasis id="5001B9EA47A5BB7C2DF0CA2534CF6C65" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">M.P. Petrov</emphasis>
s.n. [27/5/1957]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FC6839FE0798B6AAC3C98F004A49BEE1" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A6AA920C060F5777218AB817E1B8676D" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5AB4860C2B7F76CDD443406FA72724D2" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="32A25945A60CFC0BCB0AACB0CEFBFE26" authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 549. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ammannii" order="Solanales" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ammannii">
<emphasis id="0A5216217155CDA7CBEDC0760A7D1071" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Convolvulus ammannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but flowers all terminal, the stem somewhat woody and slightly divaricate, the sepals and corolla both significantly longer and leaves strictly linear.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C6659BA279E291C0DA41A9A9F98614FE" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">This species is only known from two collections from the Hwang Ho (Yellow River) region of north China. The Petrov collection at LE has entirely solitary terminal flowers, while in the Purdom collection (K) some branches terminate in solitary flowers while in others the flowers are arranged in terminal dichasial cymes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B76BDE631BCA7BC0E38B984407A18D1" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
This species may be rare and threatened or simply overlooked but for the time being should be classified as Data Deficient (DD) within 
<bibRefCitation id="66A8412877A64E2CF140E8E1D96D5C31" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="International Union for the Conservation of Nature, Gland, Switzerland" pageId="204" pageNumber="205" refId="B159" refString="IUCN, 2012. Guidelines for application of IUCN Red List Criteria at Regional and National Levels. International Union for the Conservation of Nature, Gland, Switzerland" title="Guidelines for application of IUCN Red List Criteria at Regional and National Levels" year="2012">IUCN (2012)</bibRefCitation>
guidelines. The epithet &quot; 
<emphasis id="C86427D918F956C343DA14204E290625" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">xanthopotamicus</emphasis>
&quot; refers to the Yellow River or Hwang Ho to whose valley system it is restricted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
